"struct:0705842b4dd0f200eec0c0b4855590b0"
"struct"
"faultyTarget"
"faultyTarget"
"pkg/dbcopy/partial_failure_test.go"
"go"
66
74
5
1
"faultyTarget wraps a real *dalgo2ingitdb.Database and intercepts every\nRunReadwriteTransaction call. When a transaction's inner tx.InsertMulti\nis called for the configured faultTable, the wrapper increments an\ninsert counter; on the (faultAfter+1)-th call, it returns\nerrInjectedInsertFailure WITHOUT delegating to the real tx — so the\nreal driver never sees the failing batch, and the underlying ingitdb\nstate contains only the rows from the prior successful flushes.\n\nAll other methods (CreateCollection, ListCollections, etc.) are\npromoted from the embedded *dalgo2ingitdb.Database verbatim. The\nengine's type assertions for ddl.SchemaModifier and\ndbschema.SchemaReader succeed against *faultyTarget because the\ndriver's methods are inherited at compile time."
""
null
false
false
false
false
null
null
""
